text:
Relatively large and spacious canteen in the Eunos Industrial Estate. Tables are spaced out well with sufficient walking space. Not busy after lunch hours. Ventilation is quite goof with plenty of ceiling fans. Beer here is on the high side with a bottle of Tiger beer going for $8.
Service is quick.

Cleanliness not the best but food is cheap and not bad.

Recommend the roast meats stall (cheap) the yong tau foo (some varieties but can get with laksa or lor mee), the fish soup (add fish roe) and the zichar stalls.
I had a the fish soup here and it was nice.  The place was a bit hot though but it doesn't feel claustrophobic.
Rare find in an industrial estate. The salmon fish porridge is very fresh and tasty. Itâ€™s hot during mid-day though.

Chicken rice was not bad! Price is super reasonable with a good sized portion. Atmosphere is very nostalgic, but quite abit of flies.

Good teh-o and kopi
